President Obama has announced his intent to appoint and designate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Toni L. Griffin and Alex Krieger as members of the Commission of Fine Arts, Jacqueline K. Barton as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Anne Case as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science, Merrill Friedman as a member of the President's Committee for People with Intellectual Disabilities, Reuben Brigety as a member of the National Security Education Board, Gene Shawcroft as a member of the Utah Reclamation Mitigation and Conservation Commission, and Christine Fox as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Naval Academy. These individuals bring a wealth of experience and dedication to their roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them.